  "riddle": "1. Seek the Belgian composer and educator whose talents earned him the nation's prestigious music award known as the Prix de Rome. What year did this honor grace his career?\n\n2. There exists a bustling hub known for its role as a federal region of Belgium, containing the beating heart of the nation. Dive into its demographics and reveal the number of its inhabitants.\n\n3. This nation's tapestry is woven with history, chocolate, and exquisite lace — find how many call this entire kingdom home.\n\n4. Within the vast population you uncovered in the previous step, a digital mystery lies: how many times does the numeral one appear when its quantity is coded in binary?\n\n5. Pinpoint the city nestled in Flanders, renowned for its diamond trade, whose elevated stature above sea level is quietly noted in its vital statistics.\n\n6. In the quest for heights, consult the almighty map. From this urban jewel of Flanders, ascertain once more the vertical distance between terra firma and the sky above.\n\n7. How many havens of respite — from quaint B&Bs to opulent suites — welcome weary travelers near this Flemish metropolis?\n\n8. Combine the results of your elevation and hotel search from clues 6 and 7. What singular digit results from the dance between their differences?\n\n9. Take the height you found in clue 5 and unravel how many distinct whole numbers can divide it without a remainder.\n\n10. In the age when knights sought glory, a period of ecclesiastical discord rent Europe asunder. For how many years did this Papal Schism test the continent's unity?\n\n11. If you venture to the charming city that crowns East Flanders, a numerical designation awaits within its vital data. Reveal the series of tones that connect to its phones.\n\n12. If one were to ascend, rather than traverse, how high above the sea does this ancient capital stand?\n\n13. Count the culinary establishments nestled near this historic haven. How many places allow you to break bread and share stories?\n\n14. With the heights of clue 12 and culinary count of clue 13 in hand, what is the outcome when you measure the space between them?\n\n15. The medieval sentinel of this city, standing for centuries, invites both locals and travelers. But how do the stars align in the opinions of those who've gazed upon its majesty?\n\n16. To conclude your journey, bring together the calculations from clues 5 and 6. Subtract and find the remainder when divided by ten. Your final query: what singular figure emerges from this arithmetic dance?",
